One more person has died from the coronavirus in South Africa,bringing the death toll to 12. The Department of Health said that the latest person to die from the virus is a 57-year-old man from the Western Cape. He had been admitted yesterday suffering from diabetes and heart related diseases. The number of infections is 1686 with an increase of 81 from yesterday,according to the statement released by Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize.Almost 60 000 tests have been conducted across Mzansi.